  "text": "\"Philosophically speaking, the difference in the type of reasoning behind semi-group lower bounds and group lower bounds is parallel to the difference between understanding geometry and understanding computation. Since we have been vastly more successful at the former, it should not come as a surprise that progress outside the semi-group model has been extremely slow [CITATION_1] .\"",
